# Project Conventions

## Standing Rule: Continuous Documentation

After every implementation session, you MUST update:
1. `.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc` with any new visual/UX patterns
2. `.cursor/rules/project-conventions.mdc` with any new structural/technical patterns
3. `DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` with comprehensive details for new components or patterns

This is not optional. Skipping documentation creates drift between pages. Every design decision must be recorded so the next page stays aligned.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router) with React 19
- **Content**: Fumadocs MDX (fumadocs-mdx v14, fumadocs-core v16, fumadocs-ui v16)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 with Fumadocs neutral theme preset
- **Fonts**: Inter (body) + Instrument Serif (display), loaded via `next/font/google`
- **Deployment**: Vercel (standard Next.js, no special config)

## Content Structure
- Content lives in `content/docs/` as `.mdx` files with YAML frontmatter (`title`, `description`)
- Navigation is controlled by `meta.json` files in each content folder
- Content source configured in `source.config.ts`, loaded via `lib/source.ts`
- Reading order defined in `lib/reading-order.ts` (30-page canonical sequence)
- The manuscript source of truth lives in a separate repo (`trilogy-project/manuscript/`)

## IDEAL Framework (Content Organization)
- 5 stages: Identify, Diagnose, Earn, Assess, Lock
- 3 modules per stage (15 total) + 5 stage openings + 5 stage closings
- 2 extensions + 1 closing chapter = 30 content pages total
- Sidebar order: Overview > Stage 1-5 > Extensions > Closing

## Typography Rules
- **No em dashes.** Never use `---` (em dash), `&mdash;`, or the Unicode em dash character anywhere in this project. Use double hyphens `--` instead. This applies to all code, content, and copy.

## Route Structure
- `/` -- Landing page (`app/(home)/page.tsx`)
- `/docs` -- Documentation index (Introduction)
- `/docs/[...slug]` -- All doc pages
- `/api/search` -- Orama search endpoint

## File Organization
- `app/(home)/` -- Landing page and home layout
- `app/docs/` -- Documentation layout and catch-all page
- `app/docs/sidebar-components.tsx` -- Client components for sidebar (stage dots, progress icons)
- `app/api/` -- API routes (search)
- `content/docs/` -- MDX content files + meta.json navigation
- `lib/source.ts` -- Fumadocs content loader
- `lib/reading-order.ts` -- Canonical 30-page reading sequence
- `lib/page-utils.ts` -- Stage color mapping, module index computation
- `lib/progress.tsx` -- ProgressProvider context (localStorage + cookie)
- `components/mdx.tsx` -- Base MDX component overrides
- `components/mdx-enhanced.tsx` -- Pattern-detecting enhanced strong component
- `components/docs-components.tsx` -- ScrollProgress, PageMeta (client)
- `components/progress-gate.tsx` -- ProgressGate + ReadingTracker (client)
- `scripts/` -- Build and audit scripts

## Content Frontmatter
Every MDX file requires:
```yaml
---
title: "Page Title"
description: "One-line description for SEO and page header."
---
```

Optional frontmatter:
- `full: true` -- removes max-width constraint on docs body (use when page has Cards or wide content)

## Content Editing Rules
- Do NOT duplicate the frontmatter title as an H1 or H2 in the body
- Remove publisher/internal metadata (back cover copy, one-page pitches, author structural notes)
- Use `<Callout>` components for key concepts, rules, and framing statements
- Use `<Cards>` + `<Card>` for navigation grids, persona routing, and stage overviews
- Bold labels (`**Exercise:**`, `**Output for this module**`, `**Template**`) are auto-detected and styled by the enhanced MDX component -- do not change their text patterns
- Link to other pages with relative paths: `[Stage 1](/docs/stage-1-identify)`
- All content copy must come from the manuscript source of truth -- do not invent new language

## Known MDX Caveats
- `# ` at the start of a list item is parsed as a heading. Escape as `\#` or rewrite as "Number of".
- The `compiled/Chapters.md` legacy file from the manuscript is excluded from the doc site.
- Fumadocs renders the frontmatter `title` as the page H1. Do not include an H1 in the MDX body.
- JSX components in MDX (`<Card>`, `<Callout>`, etc.) must be registered in the MDX component map or be default Fumadocs components.

## Progress System
- Sequential gating: page N+1 unlocks when page N is scrolled to 85%
- Storage: `tvp-progress` key in localStorage + cookie
- Context: `ProgressProvider` wraps the docs layout
- Gate: `ProgressGate` component wraps page content, redirects if locked
- Tracker: `ReadingTracker` component monitors scroll depth
- Reset: `resetProgress()` function available from `useProgress()` hook